Key Match Events: Bas de Leede is the Man of the Match
Vikramjit Singh and Max O'Dowd provided a great start for Netherlands in their pursuit of 122
Pre-Game Insights: Scott Edwards, the captain of the Netherlands, says that they don't wanna be known as the team that leaves it late but is stoked with the win.
Gerhard Erasmus, the skipper of Namibia, says that they could not keep things tight in the field which made it easier for the opposition.
Gerhard Erasmus won the toss and elected to bat first.
Post-Match Reflections: Scott Edwards, the captain of the Netherlands, says that they did well to get the runs at the top and they knew Namibia had strong death bowlers but they managed to get over the line and is happy with the opportunity they have given themselves to make the next round.
Gerhard Erasmus, the skipper of Namibia, says that they lacked with the blade, and probably even Netherlands struggled with the same but they ran well.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Namibia lost as many as 3 wickets inside the Powerplay
Jan Frylinck kept the steady knock for Namibia
Max O'Dowd and Vikramjit Singh stitched a 59-run partnership
Netherlands lost 3 wickets towards the end of the innings
Namibia clawed their way back into the game with quick wickets
Netherlands held their nerves and won by 5 wickets
